{"id":31706,"date":"2019-06-02T14:14:22","date_gmt":"2019-06-02T10:14:22","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=31706"},"modified":"2019-06-02T14:14:22","modified_gmt":"2019-06-02T10:14:22","slug":"everything-raised-humbled","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/02\/everything-raised-humbled\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Humility: Everything raised up in world will be humbled"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Anas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, had a camel named Al-\u2018Adba and she could not be outraced. A bedouin came riding his camel and outraced her. That was difficult for the Muslims and they said, \u201cAl-\u2018Adba has been beaten!\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Verily, it is a duty upon Allah that nothing is raised up in this world but that it will eventually be humbled<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6136<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari<\/p>\n<p>Al-Baghawi said, \u201cIn this is permission to name animals. It was the custom of the Arabs to name their animals.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sharh\u0323 al-Sunnah 8\/222<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0646\u064e\u0627\u0642\u064e\u0629\u064c \u0644\u0650\u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u062a\u064f\u0633\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0636\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0648\u064e\u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062a\u064f\u0633\u